QUESTION: Naturally hairy, often wet. Searching for wood that I can get. What am I ?
Four letters stand to make my name. Should 2 be taken, 4 remains. And should they take away 1 more, my meaning will be as before.
You can swallow me, but I can consume you too. What am I?
We are 16 in total, but can never be a king, what are we?
I wield power, yet I'm not a king; my influence spreads, but I have no wings. In me, you'll find wisdom, folly, and more; I'm passed between hands and through many doors. What am I?
With no legs, I slither and slide; with no lungs, I breathe deep inside. A master of disguise, I can change my hue; I'm both predator and prey, to name just a few. What am I?
I dance in the night, but fade in the day; I'm never held captive, try as you may. An illusion of sorts, yet there's nothing to hold; I'm often pursued, but I'm never controlled. What am I?
Though I have no heart, I can still pump; no legs, but I climb and jump. I'm always moving, never idle, and if you chase me, you'll be in a cycle. What am I?
I come in pairs, yet I'm never the same; a crucial player in a complex game. You use me daily, yet seldom with care, and without me, your path would lead nowhere. What am I?
I bind and divide, yet I have no hands; I can mark the passing of life's many sands. Invisible, I hold strong, but one small tear can make me fall and disappear. What am I?
In the darkness, I bring light, but not from the sun or moon's sight. I'm ancient and young, with no end or start; you'll find me in stories, poems, and art. What am I?
I am your guard, your armor, your shield; with me by your side, you'll never yield. I'm always there, but seldom shown; my strength depends on you alone. What am I?
I'm not alive, but I can grow; I lack a mouth, yet I can flow. I can be tamed or run wild, and my form is often beguiled. What am I?
I can be vast and infinite or small and confined; I may hold treasures, secrets, and memories combined. I can be locked, but I have no key; only you can truly set me free. What am I?

At half I am only some. When I'm full, people will turn my way. What am I?

What has four fingers and thumb, but it is not living?
What is it that no one wants, but no one wants to lose?
